  <section id="Section-Tasks-Equations">
    <title>Equations</title>
    <para>
      The Equations Page determines which &equations; will be <link
      linkend="Section-Tasks-Solver">solved</link>. As shown in <xref
      linkend="Figure-EquationsPage"/>, the page simply consists of a
      Mesh Chooser and an Equations Pane.
    </para>
    <figure id="Figure-EquationsPage">
      <title>The Equations Page</title>
      <mediaobject>
	<imageobject>
	  <imagedata fileref="FIGURES/gui/equations_page.png"
	    format="PNG"/>
	</imageobject>
	<imageobject>
	  <imagedata fileref="FIGURES/gui/equations_page.eps"
	    format="EPS"/>
	</imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    <para>
      Clicking on the <quote><guilabel>active</guilabel></quote>
      button next to an &equation; name in the Equations Pane <link
      linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Mesh.Equation.Activate">activates</link>
      the &equation;, meaning that it will be solved by <xref
      linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Solver.Solve"/>.  Clicking again <link
      linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Mesh.Equation.Deactivate">deactivates</link>
      the equation.
    </para>
    <para>
      The <link
      linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Mesh.Copy_Equation_State"><guibutton>Copy
      Equation State</guibutton></link> button copies the Equation
      Pane settings from the currently selected &mesh; into a
      specified target &mesh;.  The target is selected in a dialog
      box.
    </para>

  </section>
    

